    - [ ] Uses a Map.<K, V> internally.
    - [ ] Supports weak elements.
    - [ ] Unlike a Map, accessing properties never throws a ReferenceError. It returns either false or true; that is mainly why Set was introduced, since Map based sets work worse (e.g. has value is basically 'k in set && set[k]')
